- Use short, clear sentences.\
- Avoid corporate speak entirely.\
- Sound blue-collar, friendly, and experienced.\
- Ask clarifying questions.\
- Keep friction low.\
- Always know the \'93next best step.\'94\
- Bias toward completing the order.\
\
